Package org.teatrove.trove.file

Interface Summary
DataFileBuffer Extends the regular FileBuffer interface for providing I/O operations on primitive data types.
FileBuffer Interface for accessing and modifying the contents of a file.
FileRepository Allows files to be created with automatically assigned identifiers.
FileRepository.Iterator  
TxFileBuffer TxFileBuffer supports transactions.
 

Class Summary
Bitlist Various utilities for operating on a file at the bit level.
FileBufferInputStream An InputStream interface to a FileBuffer which supports marking and repositioning.
FileBufferOutputStream An OutputStream interface to a FileBuffer which supports repositioning.
MultiplexFile MultiplexFile is a growable list of FileBuffers, stored completely within another FileBuffer.
MultiplexFileRepository  
NonTxFileBuffer A TxFileBuffer implementation that satisfies the API requirements, but doesn't actually do anything useful for transactions.
RandomAccessFileBuffer A FileBufferImplementation that calls into the standard Java RandomAccessFile class.
ReadOnlyFileBuffer  
SystemFileBuffer An implementation of FileBuffer that makes direct calls into the operating system's file I/O functions.
TaggedTxFileBuffer A simple TxFileBuffer implementation that uses a tag bit to indicate if the file is in a clean state.
 

Exception Summary
CorruptFileException Exception thrown if file corruption has been detected.
